## Configurar o Nginx

- Após a instalação do CIPI, acessar e adicionar na conf default do Nginx

sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default

server {
    root /var/www/html/public;
    add_header X-Frame-Options "SAMEORIGIN";
    add_header X-XSS-Protection "1; mode=block";
    add_header X-Content-Type-Options "nosniff";
    client_body_timeout 10s;
    client_header_timeout 10s;
    client_max_body_size 256M;
    index index.html index.php;
    charset utf-8;
    server_tokens off;
    server_name ribamar.net.br www.ribamar.net.br;
    location / {
        try_files   $uri     $uri/  /index.php?$query_string;
    }
    location = /favicon.ico { access_log off; log_not_found off; }
    location = /robots.txt  { access_log off; log_not_found off; }
    error_page 404 /index.php;
    location ~ \.php$ {
        include snippets/fastcgi-php.conf;
        fastcgi_pass unix:/var/run/php/php8.0-fpm.sock;
    }
    location ~ /\.(?!well-known).* {
        deny all;
    }

    listen [::]:443 ssl ipv6only=on; # managed by Certbot
    listen 443 ssl; # managed by Certbot
    ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/ribamar.net.br/fullchain.pem; # managed by Certbot
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/ribamar.net.br/privkey.pem; # managed by Certbot
    include /etc/letsencrypt/options-ssl-nginx.conf; # managed by Certbot
    ssl_dhparam /etc/letsencrypt/ssl-dhparams.pem; # managed by Certbot
}

Apenas adicionei a linha

server_name ribamar.net.br www.ribamar.net.br;

sudo service nginx restart

## Instalar o Certbot

No ribamar.net.br, que está associado a este servidor do CIPI

sudo snap install core; sudo snap refresh core
sudo ln -s /snap/bin/certbot /usr/bin/certbot
sudo certbot --nginx

